UID:6c32e0d2-9bb6-4f6b-895f-284dce2ce998@travel-concierge
DESCRIPTION:**Day 1**\n- 07:30 🍳 Breakfast: Kachoris at Rawat Mishthan 
 Bhandar — try Pyaaz Kachori\, ~₹50\n- 09:30 🏛️ Morning: City Pala
 ce (open 09:30–17:30\, entry ₹300) — This majestic palace showcases 
 a blend of Rajput and Mughal architecture\, with intricate designs and bea
 utiful gardens. The palace also houses a museum with a collection of royal
  artifacts and weaponry.\n  → Transport: Hire an auto-rickshaw from the 
 hotel for ₹100\, 20-minute ride\n- 13:00 🍽️ Lunch: Laxmi Mishtan Bh
 andar — recommended dish: Dal Baati Churma\, ~₹200\n- 15:00 🎭 After
 noon: Jantar Mantar (open 09:00–16:30\, entry ₹50) — This ancient as
 tronomical observatory features massive sundials and instruments that were
  used to measure time and track celestial movements. The complex is a test
 ament to the ingenuity of the Rajput kings and their interest in astronomy
 .\n  → Transport: Walk from City Palace\, 10-minute walk\n- 19:00 🌅 S
 unset: Nahargarh Fort — Watch the sunset over the city from this histori
 c fort\, which offers breathtaking views of Jaipur.\n- 20:00 🍷 Dinner: 
 Chokhi Dhani — must-try: Laal Maans\, ~₹400\n- 💡 Local tip: Try the
  local street food at Johri Bazaar\, where you can find delicious snacks a
 nd sweets.\n- ☔ Indoor backup: Visit the Albert Hall Museum (open 09:00
 –17:30\, entry ₹40)\, which features a collection of artifacts\, paint
 ings\, and sculptures.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Day 2: try Pyaaz Kachori\, ~₹50
