DESCRIPTION:**Day 2**\n- 07:30 🍳 Breakfast: Baker Street — try Chocol
 ate Croissant\, ~₹150\n- 09:30 🏛️ Morning: Amber Fort (open 08:00
 –18:00\, entry ₹550) — This stunning fort is made of white marble an
 d red sandstone\, and features intricate carvings\, ornate palaces\, and b
 eautiful gardens. The fort is a testament to the rich history and architec
 ture of the Rajput kingdom.\n  → Transport: Hire a taxi from the hotel f
 or ₹500\, 30-minute ride\n- 13:00 🍽️ Lunch: 1135 AD — recommended
  dish: Murgh Tikka\, ~₹350\n- 15:00 🎭 Afternoon: Hawa Mahal (open 09:
 30–16:30\, entry ₹50) — This unique palace features a honeycomb-like
  structure with small windows\, which allowed the royal women to observe t
 he outside world without being seen. The palace is a masterpiece of Rajput
  architecture and offers stunning views of the city.\n  → Transport: Tak
 e bus number 5 from Amber Fort\, ₹20\, 45-minute ride\n- 19:00 🌅 Suns
 et: Jal Mahal — Watch the sunset over the lake from this beautiful palac
 e\, which is surrounded by water and offers stunning views.\n- 20:00 🍷 
 Dinner: OKRA — must-try: Grilled Fish\, ~₹500\n- 💡 Local tip: Take 
 a stroll through the beautiful gardens of the Kanak Vrindavan Temple\, whi
 ch features intricate carvings and stunning architecture.\n- ☔ Indoor ba
 ckup: Visit the Rajasthan Patrika Museum (open 10:00–17:00\, entry ₹20
 )\, which features a collection of artifacts and exhibits on the history a
 nd culture of Rajasthan.
END:VEVENT
