DESCRIPTION:**Day 3**\n- 07:30 🍳 Breakfast: The Glasshouse — try Panc
 akes\, ~₹200\n- 09:30 🏛️ Morning: Mehrangarh Fort (open 09:00–17:
 00\, entry ₹600) — This majestic fort is one of the largest in India a
 nd features stunning architecture\, beautiful gardens\, and a collection o
 f royal artifacts. The fort offers breathtaking views of the city and the 
 surrounding desert landscape.\n  → Transport: Take the metro from Jaipur
  to Jodhpur\, ₹500\, 5-hour ride\, then hire an auto-rickshaw for ₹100
 \, 20-minute ride\n- 13:00 🍽️ Lunch: On The Rocks — recommended dis
 h: Chicken Tikka\, ~₹300\n- 15:00 🎭 Afternoon: Umaid Bhawan Palace (o
 pen 09:00–17:00\, entry ₹100) — This stunning palace features a blen
 d of Indian and European architecture and offers stunning views of the cit
 y. The palace is now a museum and features a collection of royal artifacts
  and exhibits on the history of Jodhpur.\n  → Transport: Walk from Mehra
 ngarh Fort\, 10-minute walk\n- 19:00 🌅 Sunset: Kaylana Lake — Watch t
 he sunset over the lake from this beautiful spot\, which offers stunning v
 iews of the surrounding landscape.\n- 20:00 🍷 Dinner: Indique — must-
 try: Laal Maans\, ~₹450\n- 💡 Local tip: Take a stroll through the bea
 utiful gardens of the Mandore Gardens\, which feature intricate carvings a
 nd stunning architecture.\n- ☔ Indoor backup: Visit the Jodhpur Art Gall
 ery (open 10:00–17:00\, entry ₹20)\, which features a collection of ar
 twork and exhibits on the history and culture of Jodhpur.
END:VEVENT
